N = actual length of the stored property in bytes
                       (even if the format is 16 or 32)
I = 4 * long-offset
T = N - I
L = MINIMUM(T, 4 * long-length)
A = N - (I + L)
byte1 = N/D + min-byte1
byte2 = N\D + min-char-or-byte2
D = max-char-or-byte2 - min-char-or-byte2 + 1
L = D * (max-byte1 - min-byte1 + 1)
